5 terrain vehicle or a utility-type vehicle while operating such the all-
6 terrain vehicle or a utility-type vehicle on a highway; , and
7 (iii) Not shall not operate the all-terrain or utility-type such
8 vehicle at a speed in excess of thirty miles per hour.
9 (c) The person operating an the all-terrain vehicle or a utility-
10 type vehicle shall provide proof of such insurance coverage to any peace
11 officer requesting such proof within five days of such a request.
12 (d) When operating an all-terrain vehicle or a utility-type vehicle
13 as authorized in subsection (2) of this section, the headlight and
14 taillight of the vehicle shall be on and the vehicle shall be equipped
15 with a bicycle safety flag which extends not less than five feet above
16 ground attached to the rear of such vehicle. The bicycle safety flag
17 shall be triangular in shape with an area of not less than thirty square
18 inches and shall be day-glow in color.
19 (4) All-terrain vehicles and utility-type vehicles may be operated
20 without complying with subsection (3) of this section on highways in
21 parades which have been authorized by the State of Nebraska or any
22 department, board, commission, or political subdivision of the state.
23 (5) The crossing of a highway other than a controlled-access highway
24 with more than two marked traffic lanes shall be permitted by an all-
25 terrain vehicle or a utility-type vehicle without complying with
26 subsection (3) of this section only if:
27 (a) The crossing is made at an angle of approximately ninety degrees
28 to the direction of the highway and at a place where no obstruction
29 prevents a quick and safe crossing;
30 (b) The vehicle is brought to a complete stop before crossing the
31 shoulder or roadway of the highway;
